The '''Jordan national football team''' ({{langx|ar|منتخب الأردن لكرة القدم}}), nicknamed '''''Al Nashama''''' ({{lit|''The Chivalrous Ones''}}), represents [[Jordan]] in men's international [[Association football|football]]. It is under the jurisdiction of the [[Jordan Football Association]]. 

Jordan has played in five [[AFC Asian Cup]] tournaments, appearing in the final of a major tournament for the first time in the [[2023 AFC Asian Cup|2023]] edition, finishing as runners-up. They also finished runners-up of the [[FIFA Arab Cup]] in [[2025 FIFA Arab Cup|2025]], and have won the [[Arab Games]] twice, in [[1997 Arab Games|1997]] and [[1999 Arab Games|1999]]. The team reached the [[WAFF Championship]] final on three occasions but never won it. The country qualified for their first [[FIFA World Cup]] in [[2026 FIFA World Cup|2026]].